<p class="Core-Styles_Core-Body-Last--to-apply-extra-space-" data-content-chunk-id="5b35242c-e180-4a5d-a379-1e63439161c3"><span class="Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Serif" data-content-chunk-id="4cd49981-65ec-43bb-8710-af73140dcd72">Acolytes</span>&nbsp;are junior members of a clergy, usually answerable to a priest. They perform a variety of functions in a temple and are granted minor spellcasting power by their deities.</p>
